                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I'm opposed to using the Need Before Greed setting in WoW.  While I agree that people should only roll on stuff they can use (on the first pass), the NBG setting does not achieve that.  Rather, it only assures that Warriors can roll on more stuff than Priests (for example).  Perhaps it should be called MBC (Mail Before Cloth).  If you trust your Warriors and Paladins to only roll on things they can use, you should trust the rest of the group to do the same.  To do otherwise is insulting.
<br />

<br />
Therefore: Group Loot.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ceilon and Hawafena
<br />
