                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My usual group uses Round Robin. If you loot a green, offer it to the group to see if anyone wants as an upgrade. If they do its theirs, if they dont its yours. 
<br />

<br />
The reasons we do this is bad experience with rolling. Firstly theres the usual loot whores who roll on everything, and theres the 'oops i didnt know it was bind on pickup' as the warrior accidently rolls for that nice cloth item you could have used. The round robin itself takes care of the randoming of loot, and theres less time wasted waiting for rolls. On boss rolls, link the item to group and /random 1 100.
<br />

<br />
I group with mostly the same groups of people, but we let all newcomers know about it on joining and so far everyone has been happy. Since then theres been no loot whore complaints and nobody rolling on stuff they dont need. Plus you dont have 1 billion corpses glowing for you and have people running around trying to check them all, wasting more time, as in group loot.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
