                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Bellanfear -- That is my experience for the most part.  But there was at least one time where somebody was doing this to me and I am "pretty sure" that I was getting less than normal XP.  I'd bet he didn't get any at all, but it seems that if somebody else does *enough* damage to the mob, they can reduce the amount of xp you get.
<br />

<br />
It actually makes sense as a way to prevent the first-hit-rule from leading to a lot of powerleveling.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Ceilon and Hawafena
